The paper deals with privacy and utility in a distributed data system, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of maximal correlation as a measure of privacy also suggests a potential connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the explicit privacy scheme mentioned in the abstract could fall under the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
